Ids.Id: Caenorhabditis elegans N2 larval L4 male RNA library L4MALE6 array capture 4

Description.Title: Caenorhabditis elegans N2 larval L4 male RNA library L4MALE6 array capture 4

Comment.Paragraph: Array capture experiment to remove messages already detected in other RNAseq experiments on C. elegans N2 larva L4 male library. Embryos are placed in S-basal buffer and incubated at 25 deg over night to hatch the L1s. We then put the hatched L1s on a seeded NGM plate at 25 deg for 30 hours. At 30 hours, the resulting worms are in the L4 stage, and all are males because the hermpahrodites die due to a failure to initiate dosage compensation, as confirmed by examination under the dissecting microscope. This sample is available through the modENCODE DCC (www.modencode.org) as: L4MALE6cap2 The original N2 larva L4 library is available as DCC project: Male larva mid-L4 25dC 30 hrs post-L1 Local library name: L4MALE6cap2 Quality values are ASCII encoded Phred + 33. Flowcell 428A0AAXX was processed with GAPipeline 1.4 and is 36bp. Flowcell 61BDCAAXX was processed with GAPipeline 1.8 and is 76bp.
